events.name: ミノタウロス討伐　エリカ待機

parameters:
\n< Serena >Phew... we've arrived. This is the
place. Erika- sama!
\n< Serena >Erika-sama! Are you not here?

\n< Serena >...Huh, what a pointless thing to say.
If she's not here, there wouldn't be a
response.
\n< Erika >I'm not here~.
\n< Serena >...
エリカ HK_PT01-1
エリカ HK_PT01-1

\n< Erika >Mm- thanks for the hard work
transporting supplies. Is it Serena-chan
on supply duty today?
\n< Erika >There we go.

\n< Erika >Hehe, as lovely as ever, huh? After
crawling around in the bushes all day,
you look even cuter.

You're quite the warrior yourself,
Erika-sama.\n< Serena >

Right? Right? I spent quite a bit of
money on this. It's my pride and joy!\n< Erika >

That outfit... it's the same as the
other day... Ah, now that I think about
it, I haven't thanked you for that time
yet.\n< Serena >
Hm? Was there something?\n< Erika >

It was during the goblin incident. If it
weren't for your help, I would have been
in danger.\n< Serena >

Let me thank you again. Thank you,
Erika-sama.\n< Serena >
Eh? No... hehehe...!\n< Erika >
What is it?\n< Serena >

Ah, well, it's just... getting thanked
to my face like that.\n< Erika >

Makes me blush. Hehehe. Kinda makes my
neck itch.\n< Erika >
...Is that how it works...?\n< Serena >

\n< Serena >You yourself are quite the warrior,
Erika-sama.
\n< Erika >Oh? Looking cool?
\n< Serena >Somewhat more impressive.

\n< Serena >Considering you usually spend your time
in town dressed so shamelessly, I
wondered if you'd be the same in the
forest.

\n< Erika >Hehehe... eh? Did you just say
'shamelessly'?

\n< Erika >Well, even I know better than to go into
the forest without proper gear.

\n< Erika >Of course for battle, but also because
you can't just go trudging through the
underbrush with bare skin.
\n< Serena >Those horns are for bushwhacking too?

\n< Erika >That's right! Though it's also for
intimidation... or design... not just
purely practical.

\n< Serena >Sigh... I thought maybe you'd be serious
for once... but you never change.

\n< Erika >Laughter is life's best companion, after
all.
\n< Serena >Hm? Whose words are those?
\n< Erika >Mine.
\n< Serena >...I see...

\n< Erika >Sooo, you brought food and supplies,
right?
That's rather abrupt...\n< Serena >
Here it is.\n< Serena >

\n< Erika >Yippee! That's what I'm talking about!
Food, and...
\n< Serena >...? What's this? A metal ball...?

\n< Erika >Hmm-? No no no... that's not quite
right...
This is a "grenade."\n< Erika >

It's a device packed with gunpowder and
magic inside a metal shell. It's the
latest in military weaponry.\n< Erika >

To be precise, it's a compact version.
With this, we'll blow that Minotaur to
smithereens.\n< Erika >

It was a real pain to get my hands on
one personally... It cost a lot of money
and connections... but it finally
arrived.\n< Erika >

\n< Serena >Is our opponent so formidable that we
need military-grade weapons? This
Minotaur monster...

\n< Erika >Well... it's always best to be prepared,
right?

\n< Erika >After all, it's a big catch. You've got
to have at least one ace up your sleeve.

\n< Erika >Anyway, let's talk about something less
dangerous... like food.

\n< Erika >I miscalculated my supplies. I've been
without a meal since yesterday. Been
nibbling on some unknown mushrooms to
stave off hunger.

\n< Serena >...There's being careless, and then
there's you...

Mmmh, I smell it, I smell it. The nice
scent of fresh bread is coming from
around here.\n< Erika >

Alright! Then today, it's lunchtime with
Serena!\n< Erika >

I have no idea what you're so pleased
about. I was planning to head back home.\n< Serena >

If I hurry now, I can make it back to
town before noon.\n< Serena >
\n< Serena >I want to get another job done today.
\n< Erika >Aww... big sister is disappointed...

\n< Erika >Well, if that's the case, there's a
shortcut. I'll show you the way.
\n< Serena >Hmm? That would be helpful.
\n< Erika >Then, let's chat along the way?

\n< Serena >So that's your scheme... Well, I don't
mind that much...
